This paper discusses the task of Cross-Document Coreference Resolution (CDCR) which involves extracting structured information from unstructured/semi-structured machine-readable documents. This task is closely related to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are sub-categories of computer science (CS). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for CDCR, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of analyzing large datasets, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases).
